# PigeonLib Architecture

## Boot Sequence

```
main()  [EntryPoint.h]
  └── pg::CreateApplication()           (client-defined; registers app-specific systems)
        └── Application::Create()
              └── Init()
                    ├── Window::Create()               (platform window + graphics context)
                    ├── World::Create()                (ECS registry, clears all state)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(AudioPlaybackSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(AudioVolumeSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(CameraSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(ConfigLoaderSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(DiffusionSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(InputSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(ResourceManagerSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(SaveDataSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(SpriteAnimationSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(SpriteRenderSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(TextGenSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(TransformComposeSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(TransformResolveSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(UIControlSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(UIEventSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(UIRenderSystem)
                    ├── RegisterSystem(WindowConfigSystem)  (reaches the live Window via Application::Get())
                    ├── Renderer::Init()               (RendererAPI, RenderCommand setup)
                    ├── PushOverlay(ImGuiLayer)         [non-test builds only]
                    └── m_Initialized = true
  └── app.Run()
```

## Per-Frame Update Sequence

```
UpdateApp()
  1. Clock::Restart()           → Timestep (inter-frame delta)
  2. LayerStack::Begin()        — ImGuiLayer opens a new Dear ImGui frame
  3. LayerStack::OnUpdate(ts)   — game layers receive delta-time
  4. World::Update(ts)          — see internal sequence below
  5. LayerStack::End()          — ImGuiLayer renders accumulated ImGui draw data
  6. Window::OnUpdate()         — drains OS message queue, then SwapBuffers
```

## World::Update Internal Sequence

```
World::Update(ts)
  ├── [first frame after RegisterSystem] SortSystems()
  │     └── Kahn topological sort; edges from writeSet/inframeAddSet → readSet
  ├── m_Dispatcher.update()       — EnTT signal delivery
  ├── for each system in sorted order:
  │     └── system->Update(ts)    — via CheckedRegistryAccessor
  ├── ClearEvents()               — destroys all entities tagged EventComponent
  └── FlushDeferredRequests()
        ├── apply m_DeferredOneFrameComponents  (emplace + schedule removal)
        ├── apply m_DeferredRequests            (persistent emplaces, removes)
        └── apply m_DeferredDestroys            (entity destruction)
```

## Platform Event Flow

```
Win32 WM_* message
  └── WindowsWindow::WindowProc
        └── Application::OnEvent(Event&)
              ├── Direct: WindowClose → m_Running=false
              ├── Direct: WindowResize → Renderer::OnWindowResize, m_Minimized flag
              └── World::EmplaceExternalEvent<XxxEventComponent>()
                    └── deferred entity: visible to ECS systems in the NEXT World::Update
```

## Module Interaction Map

```
Platform
  └── implements: Window, PlatformInput, GraphicsContext, RendererAPI, Buffer, Shader, Texture
                                │ (abstract interfaces only visible above this line)
                                ▼
Core
  ├── Application          boot sequence, layer stack, OS event bridge
  ├── ConfigLoaderSystem   Assets/Engine/Config.json (+ <savedataPath>/Config.json override)  →  EngineConfigSingletonComponent  (frame 1 only)
  ├── InputSystem          input event components  →  InputStateSingletonComponent
  ├── ResourceManagerSystem  manifests (textures/fonts/shaders/ui/sounds/json/models/renderTargets/
  │                            checkpoints/loras/controlNets/openPoseSkeletons)  →  ResourceMapSingletonComponent
  │                            (frame 1); thereafter drains RegisterGeneratedTextureRequest → m_TextureMap (ADR 0008)
  ├── SaveDataSystem       EngineConfigSingletonComponent (savedata path) + SetSaveDataRequest (from app)
  │                          →  SaveDataSingletonComponent (uuid → json); loads <savedataPath>/SaveSlots/<uuid>.json
  │                            at startup, persists slot files on request
  └── WindowConfigSystem   EngineConfigSingletonComponent (window resolution/mode) + SetWindowResolutionRequest
                             →  WindowConfigSingletonComponent; applies to the live Window + persists <savedataPath>/Config.json
                                │
                                ▼
Audio
  ├── AudioVolumeSystem    EngineConfigSingletonComponent (volumes) + SetAudioVolumeRequest
  │                          →  AudioVolumeSingletonComponent (live master/sound/music volumes)
  └── AudioPlaybackSystem  ResourceMapSingletonComponent (m_SoundMap) + AudioVolumeSingletonComponent
                             + Play/Stop/Pause/ResumeAudioRequest (from app)
                             →  AudioDeviceSingletonComponent (platform mixer); voices keyed by UUID handle

Diffusion  (in-engine text-to-image; opt-in CUDA backend, ADR 0008)
  └── DiffusionSystem      GenerateImageRequest (from app) + ResourceMapSingletonComponent (checkpoint/
                             lora/controlNet paths + OpenPose skeletons) + EngineConfigSingletonComponent
                             (Generation Config defaults)
                           →  DiffusionBackendSingletonComponent (platform inference backend; sd.cpp real
                              / Testing mock) + DiffusionJobSingletonComponent (one background-worker job)
                           →  RegisterGeneratedTextureRequest → ResourceManagerSystem registers the
                              Generated Texture into m_TextureMap (the OpenPose hint is rasterized in-engine
                              from the referenced skeleton). Cross-frame, deferred — no ordering cycle.

TextGen  (in-engine text generation; opt-in CPU llama.cpp backend, ADR 0009)
  └── TextGenSystem        GenerateTextRequest (from app) + ResourceMapSingletonComponent (GGUF model
                             paths) + EngineConfigSingletonComponent (Text Generation Config defaults)
                           →  TextGenBackendSingletonComponent (platform backend; llama.cpp real /
                              Testing mock) + TextGenJobSingletonComponent (one background-worker job)
                           →  TextGenResultSingletonComponent (target UUID → completion). Unlike the
                              Diffusion result, text is not a renderer resource, so TextGenSystem is the
                              sole writer of the result store and publishes directly (no resource-map hop).

Transform
  ├── TransformResolveSystem  ResolvedTransformRequest (from app) + CameraTransformRequest
  │                           →  PositionComponent, RotationComponent, ScaleComponent, LocalBoundsComponent
  └── TransformComposeSystem  Position/Rotation/Scale/LocalBounds  →  WorldTransformComponent (matrix + sort key)
                                │ (render bridges read WorldTransformComponent)
                                ▼
Renderer
  ├── CameraSystem         SetCameraRequest (from app) + ResizeEvent + PositionComponent
  │                          →  OrthographicCameraComponent (zoom/projection) + CameraTransformRequest (pan)
  ├── SpriteAnimationSystem  SetSpriteAnimationRequest (from app) + SpriteAnimationComponent (app-authored sheet/row/speed) + time
  │                            →  SpriteComponent sub-texture (advances the sprite-sheet frame; via pg::SpriteSheet)
  ├── SpriteRenderSystem     SpriteComponent + WorldTransformComponent  →  DrawSpriteInFrameEvent (consumed by Renderer2DSystem)
  ├── Renderer3DSystem     PerspectiveCameraComponent (3D cam) + ModelComponent + WorldTransformComponent
  │                          + ResourceMapSingletonComponent (model/render-target/shader) + EngineConfigSingletonComponent
  │                          → Renderer3DDataSingletonComponent → draws models (depth-tested, flat unlit) into the
  │                            offscreen render target, whose colour buffer is a texture the 2D pass samples (ADR 0007).
  │                            Runs strictly before Renderer2DSystem (which reads its data singleton to order the passes).
  └── Renderer2DSystem
        reads:  OrthographicCameraComponent (gameplay cam), UICameraSingletonComponent (screen-space UI cam),
                EngineConfigSingletonComponent, ResourceMapSingletonComponent, Draw*InFrameEvent,
                Renderer3DDataSingletonComponent (ordering-only, see ADR 0007)
        writes: RendererDataSingletonComponent → GPU draw calls; world pass (Y-sorted, gameplay cam),
                then UI pass (UI cam, always on top)
                                ▲
                                │ (emits DrawUI*InFrameEvent + UICameraSingletonComponent)
UI  (canvas authored against a reference resolution; scaled to the window per ADR 0005)
  ├── UIControlSystem      mutation commands + JSON layouts  →  BaseComponent, ImageComponent, TextComponent, LayoutContainerComponent, UIClipComponent
  ├── UIEventSystem        InputStateSingletonComponent + RendererConfigSingletonComponent (scale factor)
  │                          →  UIOn*OneFrameComponent (front-most element only, hit-test in logical-canvas units)
  │                          →  UIInputCapturedInFrameEvent (gameplay pointer-capture signal over interactive UI)
  └── UIRenderSystem       EngineConfigSingletonComponent + WindowResizeEventComponent + BaseComponent
                             + ImageComponent/TextComponent
                             →  RendererConfigSingletonComponent (live canvas: scale factor + logical size),
                                UICameraSingletonComponent (screen-space UI camera),
                                DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent, DrawUIStringInFrameEvent
```

## Key Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Core/Application.h` | Application singleton — window, layer stack, boot sequence |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Audio/` | Audio module — SoundClip resource, abstract AudioDevice mixer, the volume + playback systems, request components (see Documentation/ModuleInfo/Audio) |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Platform/Miniaudio/MiniaudioAudioDevice.cpp` | Real audio backend (miniaudio); Testing build uses Platform/Testing/TestingAudioDevice |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/ECS/Entity.h` | ECS abstraction layer — `pg::ecs` names (`Entity`, `null`, `Registry`, `Dispatcher`, `exclude`) over the EnTT library |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/ECS/World.h` | ECS World API — registry, system registration, deferred operations |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/ECS/CheckedRegistryAccessor.h` | Accessor API — View, Get, EmplaceDeferred, EmplaceInframe, EmplaceEvent |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/ECS/System.h` | Base System class and SystemAccessDecl struct |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Transform/` | Transform components (Position/Rotation/Scale/LocalBounds/WorldTransform), the resolve + compose systems, and the request types (ADR 0003) |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Renderer/Sprite*.{h,cpp}` | World-space sprites: SpriteComponent (texture + UV sub-rect), SpriteSheet value type (grid→UV), SpriteAnimationSystem (advances the sprite-sheet frame from SetSpriteAnimationRequest), SpriteRenderSystem (emits DrawSpriteInFrameEvent). Engine owns the logic; the app sets the data + emits the request |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Renderer/Model.{h,cpp}` | 3D model resource: parses a Wavefront .obj into CPU-side triangle geometry (ModelVertex list + index list); loaded by ResourceManagerSystem into ResourceMapSingletonComponent::m_ModelMap. ModelComponent.h references a loaded model by UUID for world-space 3D scene authoring |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Renderer/Renderer3DSystem.*` | 3D render pass: draws ModelComponent entities (perspective-projected, depth-tested, flat unlit) into an offscreen render target before the 2D pass; owns Renderer3DDataSingletonComponent (GPU buffers + model shader). The render target's colour buffer is a texture the 2D pass samples (ADR 0007) |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Renderer/PerspectiveCamera.{h,cpp}` | The 3D camera value type (perspective projection + look-at view, left-handed, zero-to-one depth); carried by PerspectiveCameraComponent, authored by the app like the 2D OrthographicCamera |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Renderer/RenderTarget.h` | Abstract offscreen draw surface (colour texture + depth buffer); `RenderTarget::Create` selects the DirectX11 backend (`Platform/DirectX11/Dx11RenderTarget`) for real builds and a no-op mock (`Platform/Testing/TestingRenderTarget`) for tests. Bound via RenderCommand::Begin/EndRenderTarget |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Core/WindowConfigSystem.*` | Window resolution/mode: seeds + owns WindowConfigSingletonComponent, applies to the live Window, persists savedata Config.json (ADR 0004) |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Core/SaveDataSystem.*` | Save-data resource: loads <savedataPath>/SaveSlots/<uuid>.json into SaveDataSingletonComponent at startup; applies + persists SetSaveDataRequest slot updates from the app |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Core/FileUtils.*` | Shared text-file read/write/exists helpers used by the config loader and writer |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Core/Window.h` | Abstract window — `ApplyWindowConfig(width, height, mode)` resizes / switches windowed↔borderless-fullscreen |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Diffusion/` | Text-to-image module (ADR 0008): OpenPoseSkeleton resource + OpenPoseHint rasterizer, DiffusionBackend abstraction + DiffusionJobParams/Image, DiffusionSystem (worker-thread job runner), GenerateImageRequest/RegisterGeneratedTextureRequest components (see Documentation/ModuleInfo/Diffusion) |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Platform/StableDiffusion/StableDiffusionCppBackend.cpp` | Real stable-diffusion.cpp (CUDA) backend, active only under `-DPG_ENABLE_DIFFUSION=ON`; inert otherwise. Testing build uses Platform/Testing/TestingDiffusionBackend |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/TextGen/` | In-engine text-generation module (ADR 0009): TextGenBackend abstraction + TextGenParams, TextGenSystem (worker-thread job runner), the GenerateTextRequest component, and the backend/job/result singletons (see Documentation/ModuleInfo/TextGen) |
| `Code/PigeonLib/Platform/Llama/LlamaCppBackend.cpp` | Real llama.cpp (CPU) text-generation backend, active only under `-DPG_ENABLE_TEXTGEN=ON`; inert otherwise. Testing build uses Platform/Testing/TestingTextGenBackend |
| `Code/SandboxApp/Sandbox2D.cpp` | Entry point — CreateApplication() + client system registration |
